    "rationale": "This is a classic and simple example of the Hofmann-Löffler-Freytag reaction. N-chloro-N-methylbutylamine undergoes a 1,5-hydrogen atom transfer via a nitrogen-centered radical, generated under acidic conditions (often with light or heat). The resulting carbon-centered radical then abstracts the chlorine atom, forming a \u03b4-chloroamine. Subsequent intramolecular nucleophilic substitution, typically induced by a base (often implicitly present or added, like NaOH after the initial steps), leads to the formation of N-methylpyrrolidine. This example clearly demonstrates the key C-H functionalization at a remote (delta) position and subsequent cyclization to form a five-membered ring, which is characteristic of the reaction.",
